snippet.textDisplay:
I came back into the comments feed to apologise for a comment I made yesterday. I felt the UK Govt. didn't care about the elderly. I was WRONG for believing that and I'm glad my comment was removed.
I'm truly sorry for what I said as I was worried about the elderly in my own family including my dear mum but that's no excuse.
On reflection and following today's news, I can see that THEY DO CARE. I can clearly see now that they are trying to stop the spread of this virus to save the elderly's lives. They also don't want our cherished NHS to buckle under the strain and have to turn people away due to hospitals being full, no ventilators and people ending up dying at home. We ALL really do have to be responsible and do our bit. Self interest has to go out the window. I know that being isolated for 3 months isn't going to be pleasant for ANYONE, but the alternative is far, far worse. This disease, fear, panic, anxiety isn't going to last forever. It's a temporary problem, albeit a huge problem but it's still temporary. A year or so from now there'll be a vaccine, the economy WILL RECOVER, it always does. If we all don't listen to the Govt. and end up catching this disease, we may never recover. The same it will be if we end up losing family members, we could even be the ones who pass the disease on to them, the devastating impact and/or guilt will destroy us. We must ensure our senior citizens self isolate for 12 wks, or longer if instructed to do so. We must quarantine our entire households if one person shows symptoms, even if we don't become symptomatic, we must be responsible and quarantine for at least 14 days.
If we do those things then the hospitals won't run out of beds, medication, ventilators. It will cope and we will survive.......... Please God, help us in our time of need 🙏.

The solution is glaringly simple and obvious. Declare a national lock-down. Everyone isolate himself. Avoid going out. Plan you weekly needs and purchases, so that you only go out 1 or 2 times each week for your essentials. Suspend your fun and freedoms for now.

There is a small chance you may die, but the virus you have will die with you and not live on to kill more people.

Once humanity has vanquished this virus, everyone can rejoice and be wiser.
